SYSTEM DESCRIPTION
========================================

The system is a wizard-based ETL configuration UI built with:

- React 18
- TypeScript
- Enterprise internal tool
- Backend provides schema registry + entity definitions
- Backend also provides configured sink options

The wizard includes:

---------------------------------------------------
STEP 1 – File Upload
---------------------------------------------------

- Upload JSON or CSV via drag & drop
- Detect file type
- Extract schema only (do NOT render raw JSON)
- Preserve JSON hierarchy
- Infer CSV schema
- Must handle very large files efficiently
- Use streaming parsing and Web Workers if needed
- Persist detected fileType in global state

---------------------------------------------------
STEP 2 – Metadata Configuration
---------------------------------------------------

- productSource
- productType
- team
- environment
- extensible key-value metadata

Common format config:
- File Encoding
- Date Default Format

If JSON:
- Root Path selector

If CSV:
- Column Delimiter (required)
- Row Delimiter (required)
- Presets + custom input

Must validate conditionally based on fileType.

---------------------------------------------------
STEP 3 – Field Mapping (MOST COMPLEX PART)
---------------------------------------------------

Visual canvas-based mapping system.

Layout:
- Left: Source hierarchical tree (virtualized)
- Right: Target entity tree
- Center: Interactive mapping canvas

Requirements:

- Draggable source and target nodes
- Directional edge (source → target)
- Each edge has independent rule properties
- Cascading right-click context menus
- Array handling rules
- Null handling rules
- Validation constraints
- Notes per mapping
- Auto-map suggestions
- Required field validation
- Type mismatch detection
- Zoom + pan
- Edge redraw only on node movement
- Clean memory handling
- Support 1,000+ mappings without performance degradation

---------------------------------------------------
STEP 4 – Transformations
---------------------------------------------------

- Ordered per field
- Type aware
- Support custom expressions
- Integrated with mapping output model
- Validate transformation chains

---------------------------------------------------
STEP 5 – Filters
---------------------------------------------------

- Rule builder with nested AND/OR groups
- Tree-based filter model
- Type-aware operators
- Real-time validation
- Efficient serialization

---------------------------------------------------
STEP 6 – Output Configuration
---------------------------------------------------

This step defines the pipeline sink.

UI Requirements:

- Dropdown (select) for sink type
- Sink options are provided by backend configuration
- Example sink types:
  - Kafka
  - RabbitMQ
  - File Storage
  - HTTP Endpoint
  - Database

Dynamic behavior:

- After selecting sinkType, dynamically render additional input fields specific to that sink.

Minimum required behavior:

If sinkType = Kafka:
  - Topic Name (required)
  - Optional partition strategy

If sinkType = RabbitMQ:
  - Queue Name (required)

If sinkType = File:
  - Output Path (required)
  - File Format (JSON/CSV/Parquet)

General Rules:

- Topic / Queue / Path field is required depending on sinkType
- Dynamic form rendering based on selected sink
- Validation must adapt dynamically
- Sink configuration must be stored as part of ETLDefinition
- Sink type must support future plugin-based extension

